.TH "hsi_register_board_info" 9 "hsi_register_board_info" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
hsi_register_board_info \- Register HSI clients information
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" hsi_register_board_info
.BI "(struct hsi_board_info const *info "  ","
.BI "unsigned int len "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "info" 12
Array of HSI clients on the board
.IP "len" 12
Length of the array
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
HSI clients are statically declared and registered on board files.

HSI clients will be automatically registered to the HSI bus once the
controller and the port where the clients wishes to attach are registered
to it.

Return -errno on failure, 0 on success.
